The '''Archibald Historical Museum''' was a museum located in [[Manitou, Manitoba|Manitou]], [[Manitoba]]. It was founded as an archive of books and photographs from the area. The museum was surrounded by several historical buildings that have been relocated and restored. The museum was founded by the William Wallcraft. The museum was located two miles east of La Riviere and four miles north off No. 3 highway, in the Rural Municipality of Pembina.

Two of the buildings are particularly significant as [[Nellie McClung]], a Canadian feminist, resided in them.<ref>{{ cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/sites/archibaldmuseum.shtml | title = Historic Sites of Manitoba: Archibald Museum (RM of Pembina) | publisher=www.mhs.mb.ca | date = August 30, 2012 | accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref>

The museum closed in 2016.

