'''Paul Augé''' (4 July 1881, [[L'Isle-Jourdain, Gers|L'Isle-Jourdain]] – 23 July 1951, [[Cabourg]]) was a 20th-century French publisher, [[Romance studies|romanist]] and [[lexicographer]]. In 1920, Paul Augé took over the publishing of the dictionary and lexicum of the [[Éditions Larousse]] from his father [[Claude Augé]].
